gomodel:SYNGO_5523  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: While we could not find a controlled study specifically for CLTB, we here infer its role in synaptic vesicle endocytosis based on evidence for CLTA and the similarities between both clathrin light chains. Clathrin light chain B (CLTB, LCb) is highly similar to light chain A (CLTA, LCa), polymorphic, and shares repeated heptad motifs (PMID:3563513).\n\n\"Several lines of evidence argue that the transient fluorescence increase of EGFP-LCa1 (clathrin light chain a, gene: CLTA) observed in synaptic boutons during stimulation reflects formation and disassembly of coated pits and is a direct measure of clathrin-mediated endocytosis in hippocampal synapses.\n\nFirst, EGFP-LCa1 inserts into structurally and functionally active coated pits in HEK cells (Fig. 1A,B).\n\nSecond, reversible transient increases of fluorescence intensity are only observed during stimulation and are restricted to synaptic boutons. Adjacent axonal segments displayed small temporary decreases instead, such that the integrated fluorescence intensity along the axon remained nearly unchanged (Figs. 3D, 4A,B).\n\nThird, by estimating the local diffusion constant (between 0.13 and 0.44 μm2/sec) (Fig. 6D), we could show that this diffusional redistribution is sufficiently fast to be not rate-limiting, because most of the exchange occurs over a small distance (~1 μm), and the axon volume is large compared with the volume of the boutons.\n\nFourth, if the signal was caused by a transient volume change, the same results should be obtained with overexpression of EGFP alone.\n\nFifth, simulations based on a minimal model of LCa1 reaction and diffusion very faithfully predict the fluorescence changes observed in boutons and axons (Fig. 5B,C).\n\nWe conclude that we were able to measure clathrin-mediated endocytosis in CNS synapses in real time.\". Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Hippocampal neurons from regions CA1-CA3 of 1- to 3-d-old Wistar rats were cultured according to previous protocols\"\n\n\"Rat clathrin light chain (LCa1) was amplified by PCR from hippocampal cDNA\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5523" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

